---CHUNK---
Document: CharFXTransform
Path: godot/classes/class_charfxtransform.rst
Summary: Defines the properties available for character effects transformations.

Properties:
* color (Color): The color of the character effect. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1).
* elapsed_time (float): The time elapsed since the effect started. Default: 0.0.
* env (Dictionary): Environment settings for the character effect. Default: {}.
* font (RID): The RID of the font used for the character. Default: RID().
* glyph_count (int): The total number of glyphs in the character. Default: 0.
* glyph_flags (int): Flags that modify glyph behavior. Default: 0.
* glyph_index (int): The index of the current glyph. Default: 0.
* offset (Vector2): The offset applied to the character's position. Default: Vector2(0, 0).
* outline (bool): Whether the character effect includes an outline. Default: false.
* range (Vector2i): The range of glyph indices affected by the effect. Default: Vector2i(0, 0).
* relative_index (int): The relative index of the character within a sequence. Default: 0.
* transform (Transform2D): The 2D transformation applied to the character. Default: Transform2D(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0).
* visible (bool): Whether the character effect is currently visible. Default: true.
---CHUNK---
Document: CharFXTransform
Path: godot/classes/class_charfxtransform.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the CharFXTransform class, which controls visual effects applied to individual characters in a RichTextLabel.

Property Descriptions
Property: color (Color)
Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
Method: set_color(value: Color)
Method: get_color() → Color
The color the character will be drawn with.

Property: elapsed_time (float)
Default: 0.0
Method: set_elapsed_time(value: float)
Method: get_elapsed_time() → float
The time elapsed since the RichTextLabel was added to the scene tree (in seconds). Time stops when the RichTextLabel is paused (see Node.process_mode). Resets when the text in the RichTextLabel is changed.
Note: Time still passes while the RichTextLabel is hidden.

Property: env (Dictionary)
Default: {}
Method: set_environment(value: Dictionary)
Method: get_environment() → Dictionary
Contains the arguments passed in the opening BBCode tag. By default, arguments are strings; if their contents match a type such as bool, int or float, they will be converted automatically. Color codes in the form #rrggbb or #rgb will be converted to an opaque Color. String arguments may not contain spaces, even if they're quoted. If present, quotes will also be present in the final string.
For example, the opening BBCode tag [example foo=hello bar=true baz=42 color=#ffffff] will map to the following Dictionary:
    {"foo": "hello", "bar": true, "baz": 42, "color": Color(1, 1, 1, 1)}

Property: font (RID)
Default: RID()
Method: set_font(value: RID)
Method: get_font() → RID
TextServer RID of the font used to render glyph, this value can be used with TextServer.font_* methods to retrieve font information.
Note: Read-only. Setting this property won't affect drawing.

Property: glyph_count (int)
Default: 0
Method: set_glyph_count(value: int)
Method: get_glyph_count() → int
Number of glyphs in the grapheme cluster. This value is set in the first glyph of a cluster.
Note: Read-only. Setting this property won't affect drawing.

Property: glyph_flags (int)
Default: 0
Method: set_glyph_flags(value: int)
Method: get_glyph_flags() → int
Glyph flags. See GraphemeFlag for more info.
Note: Read-only. Setting this property won't affect drawing.

Property: glyph_index (int)
Default: 0
Method: set_glyph_index(value: int)
Method: get_glyph_index() → int
Glyph index specific to the font. If you want to replace this glyph, use TextServer.font_get_glyph_index() with font to get a new glyph index for a single character.

Property: offset (Vector2)
Default: Vector2(0, 0)
Method: set_offset(value: Vector2)
Method: get_offset() → Vector2
The position offset the character will be drawn with (in pixels).

Property: outline (bool)
Default: false
Method: set_outline(value: bool)
Method: is_outline() → bool
If true, FX transform is called for outline drawing.
Note: Read-only. Setting this property won't affect drawing.

Property: range (Vector2i)
Default: Vector2i(0, 0)
Method: set_range(value: Vector2i)
Method: get_range() → Vector2i
Absolute character range in the string, corresponding to the glyph.
Note: Read-only. Setting this property won't affect drawing.

Property: relative_index (int)
Default: 0
Method: set_relative_index(value: int)
Method: get_relative_index() → int
The character offset of the glyph, relative to the current RichTextEffect custom block.
Note: Read-only. Setting this property won't affect drawing.

Property: transform (Transform2D)
Default: Transform2D(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0)
Method: set_transform(value: Transform2D)
Method: get_transform() → Transform2D
The current transform of the current glyph. It can be overridden (for example, by driving the position and rotation from a curve). You can also alter the existing value to apply transforms on top of other effects.

Property: visible (bool)
Default: true
Method: set_visibility(value: bool)
Method: is_visible() → bool
If true, the character will be drawn. If false, the character will be hidden. Characters around hidden characters will reflow to take the space of hidden characters. If this is not desired, set their color to Color(1, 1, 1, 0) instead.